1
00:00:00,050 --> 00:00:02,307
Most AI tutors explain more.

2
00:00:02,307 --> 00:00:05,781
But hearing an answer is not the same as understanding it.

3
00:00:05,781 --> 00:00:14,639
SishyaGuru reverses the conversation: the student teaches, the AI learns, and mastery must be supported by the student's own words.

4
00:00:14,639 --> 00:00:17,187
This is SishyaGuru: “You teach.

5
00:00:17,187 --> 00:00:18,293
AI learns.

6
00:00:18,293 --> 00:00:19,326
You master.”

7
00:00:19,326 --> 00:00:27,295
The left panel is a live concept map, the centre is the teaching conversation, and the right panel shows evidence-backed feedback.

8
00:00:27,295 --> 00:00:33,341
This public demo is clearly labelled Replay, so judges can reproduce it without an API key.

9
00:00:33,341 --> 00:00:38,557
In Live mode, a learner can press Record and teach for up to sixty seconds.

10
00:00:38,557 --> 00:00:41,165
Recording is never continuous.

11
00:00:41,165 --> 00:00:46,766
The learner stops, reviews and edits the transcript, then explicitly submits it.

12
00:00:46,766 --> 00:00:48,329
Nothing auto-submits.

13
00:00:48,329 --> 00:00:50,516
Typing always remains available.

14
00:00:50,516 --> 00:00:54,002
Here I teach how solar energy drives evaporation.

15
00:00:54,002 --> 00:00:57,920
SishyaGuru does not award mastery from fluent prose alone.

16
00:00:57,920 --> 00:01:08,545
GPT-5.6 returns a strict structured assessment, and the application accepts a mastery change only when its evidence quote is an exact substring of my lesson.

17
00:01:08,545 --> 00:01:12,043
The AI learner then asks one focused question.

18
00:01:12,043 --> 00:01:20,180
As I teach condensation, precipitation and collection, the concept map changes with text and icons, not colour alone.

19
00:01:20,180 --> 00:01:29,699
When the explanation contains a misconception, the system cites the exact wording and responds respectfully instead of pretending the concept is secure.

20
00:01:29,699 --> 00:01:34,435
At the end, the summary separates demonstrated strengths from gaps to revisit.

21
00:01:34,435 --> 00:01:39,495
It is formative guidance for this session, not a grade or permanent claim about ability.

22
00:01:39,495 --> 00:01:47,331
The Live path uses GPT-5.6 Structured Outputs with provider storage disabled for assessment requests.

23
00:01:47,331 --> 00:01:57,439
OpenAI transcription creates candidate text, and OpenAI speech renders only the already-validated follow-up question with an AI-generated voice disclosure.

24
00:01:57,439 --> 00:02:01,826
Raw audio and unsubmitted transcript candidates are ephemeral.

25
00:02:01,826 --> 00:02:07,247
Submitted reviewed text stays only in browser-local progress until Clear.

26
00:02:07,247 --> 00:02:15,937
Codex accelerated the architecture, typed contracts, bounded voice adapters, responsive interface and adversarial browser tests.

27
00:02:15,937 --> 00:02:22,608
The release passes thirty-five domain tests, twelve Replay scenarios and seven Live scenarios.

28
00:02:22,608 --> 00:02:25,216
SishyaGuru: master by teaching.
